INFLUENZA, BIRD-TO-HUMAN, CHINA (HONG KONG) (23)
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Fri, 19 Dec 1997 13:07:45 -0800 (PST)
From: Ann Kimball <akimball@u.washington.edu>
[see
Influenza, bird-to-human - China (Hong Kong) (21) 971218003034]
Influenza, bird-to-human - China (Hong Kong) (22)]
I think it is crucial to remember that the first mortality was due to
Reye's syndrome, not directly to influenza. It seems from our vantage
point that there is some panic setting in among the media which will not
slow down transmission at all. So it is worthy to emphasize we have one
single influena-related mortality. To reiterate: children with influenza
should NOT be given salicylates.
---
